body:
### Findings

**High: `get_health_scores` can become permanently empty after this commit (functional regression).**

- In `modules/modul_8/Backend/Controllers/DashboardController.php`, the dashboard read-path no longer calls `HealthScoreRepository::upsert()` (good for write-on-read removal).
- But there is now no remaining caller of `HealthScoreRepository::upsert()` in Module 8 backend, so `m8_daily_health_scores` may never be populated anymore.
- Result: `action=get_health_scores` can return empty history indefinitely for active users, even when meals/water are being logged.

### Why this matters
The optimization removes write load, but it also removes the only writer for score history. That changes API behavior, not just performance characteristics.

### Suggested fix (keep performance win, restore correctness)
Move score persistence to mutation paths (`log_meal`, `delete_meal`, `log_water`, and profile-target-changing flows), not dashboard reads.

Example direction:

```php
// MealController.php (after successful meal/water mutation)
private function recomputeAndPersistDailyScore(int $userId, string $date): void
{
    $profile = $this->profiles->getByUserId($userId);
    if (!$profile) {
        return;
    }

    $summary = $this->meals->getDashboardSummaryByDate($userId, $date);

    $targets = [
        calories  => (int) $profile[daily_calorie_target],
        protein_g => (int) $profile[daily_protein_g],
        carbs_g   => (int) $profile[daily_carbs_g],
        fats_g    => (int) $profile[daily_fats_g],
    ];

    $consumed = [
        calories  => (int) $summary[meal_totals][calories],
        protein_g => (float) $summary[meal_totals][protein_g],
        carbs_g   => (float) $summary[meal_totals][carbs_g],
        fats_g    => (float) $summary[meal_totals][fats_g],
        water_ml  => (int) $summary[water_ml],
    ];

    $score = $this->nutrition->computeHealthScore($targets, $consumed);
    $this->scores->upsert($userId, $date, $score[score], $score[cal_dev], $score[macro_dev]);
}
```

Also recommend adding one integration test that logs meal/water then verifies `get_health_scores` returns at least one row for that date.
